comment_data.body:
In Android Studio 3.4, when opening a flutter web project, I see:

```
java.lang.NullPointerException
	at io.flutter.android.AndroidModuleLibraryManager.doGradleSync(AndroidModuleLibraryManager.java:206)
	at io.flutter.android.AndroidModuleLibraryManager.update(AndroidModuleLibraryManager.java:83)
	at io.flutter.android.AndroidModuleLibraryManager.updateAndroidLibraries(AndroidModuleLibraryManager.java:198)
	at com.intellij.openapi.project.DumbServiceImpl.lambda$smartInvokeLater$7(DumbServiceImpl.java:443)
	at com.intellij.openapi.application.TransactionGuardImpl$2.run(TransactionGuardImpl.java:315)
	at com.intellij.openapi.application.impl.LaterInvocator$FlushQueue.doRun(LaterInvocator.java:435)
	at com.intellij.openapi.application.impl.LaterInvocator$FlushQueue.runNextEvent(LaterInvocator.java:419)
	at com.intellij.openapi.application.impl.LaterInvocator$FlushQueue.run(LaterInvocator.java:403)
	at java.awt.event.InvocationEvent.dispatch(InvocationEvent.java:311)
	at java.awt.EventQueue.dispatchEventImpl(EventQueue.java:762)
```

Note that I do have the gradle build option (in the flutter settings) enabled.

When creating a new Flutter project, the gradle sync progress dialog for that new project shows in the project window for the previous project (the one that was open when I ran the new project wizard).
The inspector tool window is not available until an app has been run. I did prefer the previous behavior, where it was available always, even if the content was empty.

Cherry-picked into the release candidate:
- 1b911addb9c253358f4c53eb8fd96ee680c1459e (address an issue when launches would crash for bazel launches)
- e0092830607a63ad3529c6b2064a9134d44eac7b (address an NPE for flutter projects missing 'android/' subdirs)
- 40b60bebbae19c73fc76bb7c28cc13d985e5e5c0 (provision webdev for flutter web projects)
I broke the exception above out into a separate issue: https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/3412

In Android Studio canary 12 & 13 the new project wizard does not properly display its final page when creating apps and plugins. This is because of some debugging code in ModelWizard that shot-circuits the page-add logic to make it easier to debug wizard pages. I hope that will be removed be removed prior to beta.
@pq not sure if this is a blocker. This happened while connected to the corp network. I see it at home, but that's not surprising. My home network is slow. Corp should be fast.

I don't think it's a blocker though it is unfortunate that we have a timing issue here.  I have a few ideas and will take a look.

Thanks!
The sample creation banner seems to be a bit taller than needed.

Apparently the Android Studio new project wizard picks the first Flutter SDK in the list. It is easy to switch, but the default ought to be whatever is chosen for the current project (if any) or whatever was selected previously. #3432
When creating a plugin project that uses Kotlin the IDE asks the user to configure Kotlin projects. I'd rather it didn't. #3431
After doing 'flutter make-host-app-editable' from the IDE menu the IDE asks to configure the Android module. It shouldn't. #3430

Cherry-picks for 35.1:
- 8c3b9af1
- a79f57c
- 0285a4dd9515ca7be29cb30e3729d439bd0208b5 (build method guides)
- 0b000c2 (add a preference to control whether we reload when there are analysis errors)
- 1c94d9c
- 974b7d0abc1603115b4e7d2959163eb76285d179 <-- Disable closing labels when using UI guides.

Users with an analysis error in test code are unable to hot reload. https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/commit/0b000c2bdf383a3dc48280284bd78b977f76efeb introduces a workaround.

@stevemessick can we cherrypick this as well?

---

ed: added to the list above

I need the Following 3 CLs cherrypicked to land the Editor UI Guides feature.
https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/commit/a79f57c5eb1499392b7334fcdd3695388a096587
https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/commit/0285a4dd9515ca7be29cb30e3729d439bd0208b5
https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/commit/1c94d9cb5f07c8de8e9b4481d21450bab7ec037d

---
ed: added to the list above

Bad news. I would like an M35.2 branch with
https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/commit/21c6ceee83fc0142292c8de493bd10442d145920
patched in on top of the M35.1 branch. This fixes a crasher when the IntelliJ getLine helper was given too large an offset.
@stevemessick
